ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I ... would not recommend it to another student, because it's required for the department (hence any EEBers would HAVE to take it) and it wouldn't make sense for my, say, electrical engineering friends to even contemplate it. But it was fun!

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course didn't deepen my knowledge of ecology&evolutionary biology, and that is my main complaint about it. I personally would have enjoyed it more if it had been a little more academic, and less as though the faculty were presenting their latest research talk to us. Not that the talks weren't interesting, just that I didn't learn as much from them as I would have if we'd actually discussed papers.I don't think this course contributed to my dissertation/research.
